In order to confirm the surface functional groups at the GQDs surface, we performed X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS). Fig. 5
                     a shows the wide region XPS survey spectra for GQDs with a main graphite C1s peak at 287eV and an O1s peak at 534eV. O KLL peak represents the energy of the electrons ejected from the atoms due to the filling of the O 1s state (K shell) by an electron from the L shell coupled with the ejection of an electron from an L shell. Fig. 5b shows the deconvoluted C1s XPS spectrum of as prepared GQDs. The peak at 284.9eV and 285.8eV corresponds to sp2C carbon (graphitic) and sp3C carbon, while the component at 289.7eV is attributed to the π-π* shake up satellite of the 284.9eV [44]. The peaks at 286.6eV, 287.9eV, and 288.8eV respectively, are assigned to oxygen functionalities, namely CO, CO, and COOH [45]. The O/C ratio calculated from the C1s peak for GQDs is 0.83 (Table 1
                     ).
